<p>Greetings one and all and welcome to our coverage of the second Premier League weekend of the season.</p>

<p>Once again, the games are spaced out and without overlap to allow for blanket television coverage with fans still unable to get back into grounds.</p>

<p>We begin at Goodison Park watching an Everton side creating quite a buzz following some exciting summer acquisitions, with optimism soaring after last Sunday's 1-0 win at Tottenham in their season opener. </p>

<p>Today, they host newly-promoted West Bromwich Albion, whose return to the top-flight started in ominous fashion with a 3-0 home loss to Leicester. They'll hope for better here.</p>

<p>Plenty of build-up ahead for what is a 12.30pm kick-off and we will bring you all the team news in a few minutes' time. </p>
